  "response": "When disclosing an interest-free perpetual loan given by a parent to a subsidiary under Indian GAAPs, you need to consider several accounting and disclosure aspects:\n\nFor Parent Company:\n1. Investment Disclosure\n- Disclose as part of long-term investments\n- Mention the nature of the loan in notes to financial statements\n- Reflect at original transaction value\n\n2. Financial Reporting\n- Comply with Accounting Standard (AS) 12 on Related Party Disclosures\n- Disclose details in Related Party Transaction notes\n- Mention loan amount, terms, and purpose\n\nFor Subsidiary Company:\n1. Equity Classification\n- Treat as quasi-equity/additional",
